				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Short reply because I can't be here long: No, you can't update a full background in a single vblank. The fastest you can copy a byte (from ROM or normal RAM) is 8 cycles (LDA + STA), and a full background is 1024 bytes, meaning you'd need at least 8192 cycles (not considering the overhead of loops or the NMI handler) but vblank only lasts ~2273 cycles. In the best case, you're looking at 4 frames for a full background.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

