				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Is the structure of your program copied from the Nerdy Nights tutorial? The problem there isn't exactly that everything is in the NMI handler (which although not optimal, is a valid program structure - SMB for example uses it), but the fact that the game logic is placed before the PPU updates in said NMI handler. Simply inverting this order should allow you to make full use of a frame's time, with PPU updates using the first 20 scanlines (vblank) and the game logic using the remaining 240 scanlines.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

